==English==

===Alternative forms===
* catawamptious; catawampous; [[cattywampus]]; cattywampous; caliwampus; caliwampous; cankywampus; [[kittywampus]]; gittywampus; skiwampus

===Etymology===
In the fierce sense probably from {{term|catamount|lang=en}} (mountain cat).

The crooked sense may at least partly derive from the same source as the "cater" in {{term|cater-corner|lang=en}}, which some would derive from {{etyl|frm|-}} {{term|catre||four|lang=frm}}- in reference to four corners/square- from {{etyl|fro|-}} {{term|quatre||four|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|quattuor|lang=la}}. This is disputed by others, who suggest a possible {{etyl|non|-}} or other Scandinavian origin. See {{term|cater-corner|lang=en}} and {{term|cater-corner|lang=en}} for more.

